    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/11705</id>
    <published>2012-08-15T00:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-08-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/non-domestic-rates-collected-by-local-councils-in-england-2011-to-2012"/>
    <title>Non-domestic rates collected by local councils in England: 2011 to 2012</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Details of the national non-domestic rates collected by local authorities in England in 2011-12 were announced on 15 August 2012.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The latest statistics release includes data from 2007-08 to 2011-12.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The key points from the latest release are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The net rate yield (after allowances for changes in respect of previous years and reliefs) increased by 9.1 per cent to £21.0 billion in 2011-12.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The contribution to the pool (net rate yield after allowances for collection costs including losses) also increased by 9.2 per cent to £20.7 billion in 2011-12.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Between 2007-08 and 2011-12 the contribution to the pool from the local lists increased by £3.5 billion or 21 per cent.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;London accounts for 29 per cent of the contribution to the national pool while having only 15 per cent of the population.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
